Change Shape		KEY:Ghul ~ Change Shape	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A ghul's natural form is that of a donkey-hoofed undead janni. It always has the same appearance and traits in this form. It can also assume the form of a hyena. A ghul remains in one form until it chooses to assume the other one. A change in form cannot be dispelled, nor does a ghul revert to its natural form when killed. A ghul does not detect as undead while in its hyena form. A true seeing spell, however, reveals its undead form if it is in hyena form.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Cursed Claws		KEY:Ghul ~ Cursed Claws	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:A ghul's wickedly curved claws are as hard as steel and count as both cold iron and magic for the purpose of bypassing damage reduction.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Genie-Kin			KEY:Ghul ~ Genie-Kin	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:For all effects related to race, a ghul is considered a genie even though it is no longer an outsider.																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Rend				KEY:Ghul ~ Rend		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:A ghul that hits with both claw attacks latches onto the opponent's body and tears the flesh. This automatically deals an extra 2d6+6 points of damage.																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Skills			KEY:Ghul ~ Skills		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A ghul has a +4 racial bonus to Listen, Search, and Spot checks and a +8 racial bonus to Survival checks when following tracks. They have a +8 racial bonus to Climb checks and can always choose to take 10 while climbing, even if rushed or threatened.																																																													BONUS:SITUATION|Survival=Follow or identify tracks|8	BONUS:SKILL|Perception|8	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Bleed				KEY:Ghul ~ Bleed		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:Any living creature damaged by a ghul's claws continues to bleed, losing 1 hit point per round thereafter. Multiple wounds do not result in cumulative bleeding loss. A critical hit does not multiply this bleed damage. Creatures immune to critical hits are immune to the bleed damage. The bleeding can be stopped by a DC 10 Heal check.																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.62

